Description: Federal Information Processing Standard county code used as identifiers
County population estimate for 2019 from the U.S. Census Bureau
Estimates population change between 2018 and 2019

Estimates the total number of county residents living in group quarters in 2019 (e.g. nursing homes, residential treatment centers, student housing, religious convents/monasteries, correctional facilities, and hospitals)
Estimates birth rate for 2019 (live births per 1,000)
Estimates death rate for 2019 (deaths per 1,000)
Estimates natural increase rate for 2019 (birth rate - death rate)
Estimates rate of international migration for 2019
Estimates rate of domestic migration for 2019
Estimates net migration rate for 2019 (international migration + domestic migration)
Proportion of those who voted who cast ballots for President Trump in the 2016 election
Categorical variable for region according to US Census Bureau -- includes Northeast, South, Midwest, and West

Catergorical variable indicating state governor's politcal party (note that this is a binary variable; all 48 included states have governors identifying as Democrat or Republican.) Washington DC's federal district mayor (also a Democrat) is included for analysis in lieu of a governor.
Categorical variable derived from USDA's rural-urban continuum code indicating whether a county is metropolitan, metropolitan adjacent, or non-metropolitan.

Categorical variable derived from USDA's economic typography codes indicating whether a county's main source of economic activity is nonspecialized, recreation, farming, government, manufacturing, or mining.
Average cases per capita for all counties bordering a given county in the previous week
A county's latitude
A county's longitude
Average annual income for working-age county residents
Percent of county residents living below the federally identified poverty threshold
Percent of county residents who self-identify as belonging to at least one racial minority
Percentile for social vulnerability to external health risks as indexed by the CDC
Percent of county residents who do not have health insurance
Percent of county residents estimated to be smokers
Percent of county residents in two lowest levels of health condition, 'Fair' or 'Poor'
Total COVID-19 cases reported in a county before August 23rd, 2020
Total COVID-19 deaths reported in a county before August 23rd, 2020
Total COVID-19 deaths per total COVID-19 cases
